    {
      "id": "RecentPost108209",
      "post_content": "Definitely agree with Sarroth. The flavour behind these little trinkets is kind of neat, but they are unfortunately bad. MaRo has cited this cycle (see also [Wooden Sphere](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Wooden Sphere),[Crystal Rod](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Crystal Rod), [Throne of Bone](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Throne of Bone) and [Ivory Cup](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ivory Cup)) as examples of cards that are supposed to teach newer players about overvaluing certain mechanics. Gaining life seems like it is never a bad thing, and adding a little zing to each spell you cast is appealing...\n  \n   \nStill, though, if it means that you're waiting an extra turn to cast your things just so that you can gain 1 life, it slows your game badly while offering a comparatively poor reward. To realize this, you're really getting out of the spirit of the game and starting to think about its economy/mechanics... heady stuff for new players to realize on their own! ",
      "posted_by": "Leshrac_Nightwalker",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"RecentPost108209\">\n<span id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_recentPosts_postsRepeater_ctl03_post\">Definitely agree with Sarroth.  The flavour behind these little trinkets is kind of neat, but they are unfortunately bad.  MaRo has cited this cycle (see also <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Wooden Sphere\">Wooden Sphere</a>,<a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Crystal Rod\">Crystal Rod</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Throne of Bone\">Throne of Bone</a> and <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ivory Cup\">Ivory Cup</a>) as examples of cards that are supposed to teach newer players about overvaluing certain mechanics.  Gaining life seems like it is never a bad thing, and adding a little zing to each spell you cast is appealing... \r<br/> <br/>Still, though, if it means that you're waiting an extra turn to cast your things just so that you can gain 1 life, it slows your game badly while offering a comparatively poor reward.  To realize this, you're really getting out of the spirit of the game and starting to think about its economy/mechanics... heady stuff for new players to realize on their own!  </span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_recentPosts_postsRepeater_ctl03_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_recentPosts_postsRepeater_ctl03_reportAbuseLink\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: <a class=\"postedByLink\" href=\"javascript:void(0);\" id=\"PostedBy2435\">Leshrac_